article.description: Hot early shooting lifts Buffalo over Binghamton 76-50
article.headline: Hot early shooting lifts Buffalo over Binghamton 76-50
article.linkText: Hot early shooting lifts Buffalo over Binghamton 76-50
article.story: VESTAL, N.Y. -- Shannon Evans had a triple-double -- first in school history -- with 14 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists, leading a balanced attack that saw Buffalo top Binghamton 76-50 Tuesday night. Five Bulls scored in double figures with Justin Moss adding 16 points, Will Regan and Rodell Wiggington each adding 14 and Xavier Ford 11 off the bench, his fourth consecutive double-figure game. Wiggington also grabbed 11 rebounds. Buffalo (8-3) missed only two of its first eight shots as it raced away to a 15-4 lead by the first official timeout and was never threatened. The Bulls shot 50 percent in the first half with Evans scoring 13 points on three 3-pointers and four foul shots. Binghamton (1-14) has now lost 12 in a row. Willie Rodriquez led the Bearcats with 14 points and Bobby Ahearn added 12. Leading scorer Dusan Perovic, a freshman center, was not listed on the roster.
